programme.title: Alone S5E10
programme.desc: The final remaining participants face the onslaught of Mongolia's brutal winter. Relentless hunger and savage cold test them like never before.

programme.title: Monster Motor Challenge S2E2
programme.desc: A new challenge, Creek Climb, the toughest yet, gives one driver the scare of a lifetime and Bender the chance to shine.

programme.title: Forged In Fire S4E30
programme.desc: Four master smiths try to forge an iconic weapon of warfare, the trench knife. Then, two teams square off in one final battle to recreate the Chinese Dao Sword.

programme.title: Forged In Fire: Knife Or Death S2E16
programme.desc: A professional welder, martial artists and expert bladesmiths bring their custom built blades to a series of gruelling challenges that push their skills and their weapons to the limit.

programme.title: Kings Of Pain E2
programme.desc: Adam and Caveman Rob head to South Africa to face the giant Bark Scorpion, the tiny Uroplectes Scorpion, and the highly venomous Lion Fish.

programme.title: Detroit Steel E2
programme.desc: Adam exerts himself to restore a 1967 Oldsmobile 98 on a limited budget in order to satisfy his fraternity brother. Ron is given the duty of painting a 100-year-old Bi-Autogo.

programme.title: Pawn Stars S19E494
programme.desc: A set of royal British armour has Rick trying to strike a bargain. Chumlee's purchase of a US Open custom electric guitar gets no love from Rick.

programme.title: Pawn Stars S19E496
programme.desc: Rick wants to buy the first American coin ever made, but it can cost him heavily. Corey and Chum see a future for an antique 'Jetsons' cartoon lunchbox that arrives at the counter.

programme.title: Storage Wars S12E267
programme.desc: Back in Hawaiian Gardens, Emily's husband Cody misses a bid and stirs up trouble. Brandi & Jarrod put their faith in the cowboy and end up facing their mortality.

programme.title: Storage Wars S12E258
programme.desc: The buyers head to Torrance, where Mary finds clothes that don't fit her - which turns out to be a good thing. And Kenny takes a chance at being an early bird - but winds up looking more like a dodo.

programme.title: The Last Pope?
programme.desc: On the basis of Saint Malachy's 900-year-old prophesy and similar predictions by Nostradamus, people suggest that Pope Francis might be the last pope of the Catholic Church.

programme.title: Crimes That Shocked Asia E3
programme.desc: In Taiwan, a shocking double murder disrupts an idyllic farming community; in notoriously low-crime Singapore, two murder cases where the victims have been cut up send the entire nation into standstill.

programme.title: The Pickers S13E236
programme.desc: Mike and Frank uncover toy cars worth as much as the real thing and a stash of custom motorbikes with an incredible backstory.

programme.title: Car SOS S7E7
programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz are off to Kent to try and salvage a 1991 VW T4 Campervan. The vehicle belongs to 42 year old carpenter Jon who bought his mobile home several year ago with the dream of taking his wife travelling around the world. Sadly before Jon's dream came true he was diagnosed with brain cancer, his whole world ground to a halt and his plans to restore and drive his beloved van had to go on hold. Will the Car SOS team be able to help resurrect Jon's dream?

programme.title: Egypt With The World's Greatest Explorer E2
programme.desc: On the second leg of their journey, Ran and Joe spend a night inside the only surviving Wonder of the Ancient world - the Great Pyramid of Giza. On their way to Luxor their cross the 'no man's land', where few tourists venture? Much like Ran in 1969, they have a ferry to catch across the Nile. In Luxor they learn the ancient martial art called Tahtib. On their way south Ran has another test for Joe - a race across the Eastern Desert to the Red Sea.

programme.title: Explorer S3E10
programme.desc: Phil Keoghan journeys to Mexico to help tag whale sharks in order to save them. JJ Kelley explores the amazing talents and potential of super recognizers. Mariana van Zeller investigates the status of the Fukushima cleanup, and Francesca Fiorentini looks into the history of heart disease in mummies.

programme.title: Rescued E6
programme.desc: In this episode a rescue team fights through a storm to reach a fishman who's hand has been ripped through a winch. A helicopter crew pluck an injured mountaineer from an ice cliff, only to discover he's still attached to the climb ropes. And a party of mountain climbers is torn apart when a crevasse opens up, swallowing one.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E1
programme.desc: Let's look into the challenge of redesigning the Porsche 911, an automotive icon. This is the 7th generation of the car and while it clearly looks like a 911 it is virtually brand new in terms of size, design, and performance.

programme.title: Mega Food E5
programme.desc: Feeding up over 400 hungry passengers on an aircraft is just one of the challenges faced daily by the chefs at the Zurich-based Gate Gourmet. On average, they produce 50,000 meals for the visiting and home-based airlines every day, and each one is given the same care and attention as a five star meal. Get on board to discover what it takes to fill the aircrafts' galleys.

programme.title: Explorer S3E11
programme.desc: Phil Keoghan journeys to Spain to immerse himself in the world of the 'castellers,' who build human towers. Sal Masakela explores the risks of the cash only marijuana business. Mariana van Zeller investigates growing tension between grizzlies and humans. We examine why the color blue is rare in animals.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E1
programme.desc: A look at the methods used by Kim il Sung to transform North Korea into the most controlled society on Earth. After taking power in 1950, Kim's regime attempted to shape every aspect of its citizens' lives, down to their very perception of reality. Today, his grandson Kim Jung Un maintains the family tradition of wielding absolute power and brainwashing citizens to believe that the Kims are gods, and that they live in a paradise on Earth.

programme.title: Mega Air E5
programme.desc: Mega Air gets privileged access to the world's biggest air package handling facility at UPS Worldport, that ingeniously sorts up to 2 million items per night for worldwide delivery. We hitch a ride on the red-eye mail plane shuttle providing a vital service to the Channel Islands. Britain's busiest pure cargo airport is in full fire drill as fireman tackle a mock air freighter inferno and at Helsinki airport mystery freight provides a shocking outcome.

programme.title: Hell On The Highway E2
programme.desc: The tow dogs of California's Donner Pass tackle some of their most treacherous rescues and recoveries in this Hell on the Highway best-of episode. Extreme weather, broken equipment and bad drivers create hazardous working conditions for the tow operators, putting their tow trucks and lives at risk.

programme.title: Ultimate Survival WWII E4
programme.desc: Hazen Audel retraces the epic journey of an escaped POW, who evaded capture on the Nazi occupied island of Crete for more than a year during WWII.

programme.title: Mega Food E6
programme.desc: With 1,200 people, culinary operations are the biggest department in the SeaWorld Orlando theme park complex. Supplying 13 restaurants, over 50 carts and kiosks and special event dining, it's a 24-hour operation that runs 365 days of the year. And just one of these venues serves over 1,000 people an hour. Enter the SeaWorld kitchens and experience a different side of Orlando's favorite theme park.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E5
programme.desc: In 2011, almost a decade since the release of its last flagship model, the Murcielago, Lamborghini launched its latest creation – the Aventador. Megafactories visits its factory in northern Italy, to follow the story of its creation from conception to launch and to witness an incredible production process.

programme.title: Mega Air E6
programme.desc: Before lights out to start the Formula 1 season in Australia, Mega Air gets rare access behind the scenes at F1 team Haas as they rush to pack tonnes of cars and gear for air freighting. We roar back into Formula 1's past as former world champion Kimi Raikkonen's car flies to the Middle East and life-saving, temperature-controlled pharmaceuticals are given an almighty battering by the elements on a 6000 mile to Singapore.

programme.title: Hidden Gems Of Turkey E1
programme.desc: National Geographic digital nomad Andrew Evans gets under the skin of Eastern Turkey, travelling from the ruined city of Ani to the stone circles of Gobekli Tepe, considered the world's oldest temple. Travelling the same roads that oriental spice and silk traders used for thousands of years he discovers how the many civilisations that passed through the region have left their mark on the food, culture and architecture of modern Turkey.

programme.title: Dictators Rulebook E2
programme.desc: An examination of the techniques and tactics Saddam Hussein used to rise from a low level enforcer to become the supreme leader of Iraq. Through his brutal use of violence, intimidation and torture Saddam Hussein managed to rule the nation for nearly a quarter of a century until he was finally deposed by US forces during the Invasion of Iraq in 2003. Few dictators loom so large in recent history.

programme.title: Mega Factories: Supercars E5

programme.title: 1989: The Year That Made Us E3
programme.desc: What do Bart Simpson, Batman and the Little Mermaid have in common? They all became huge stars in 1989, a year that shaped Hollywood as we know it today. In this episode of Nat Geo's 6-part series, television ad film icons James Brooks and Peter Guber peel back the curtain on the world of entertainment. They reveal how the overnight success of these three characters turned the old show business into the multifaceted modern industry it is today.

programme.title: 1989: The Year That Made Us E4
programme.desc: Chuck D and Arsenio Hall discuss the pop culture revolution of 1989 that raised our collective social consciousness. Spike Lee's powerful film Do the Right Thing made a lasting impact, Public Enemy's provocative lyrics transformed Hip Hop and Arsenio Hall created a platform for a generation of stars previously ignored by late night TV. The cultural and political events of the year helped awaken mainstream audiences to the black experience.

programme.title: Car SOS S7E6
programme.desc: Tim and Fuzz are off to Forfar in Scotland to rescue the rusting wreck of a rare Talbot Sunbeam Lotus. The car was the pride and joy of former firefighter, and lifelong rally enthusiast, Jim who had planned to restore it, however a back injury not only forced him to give up his job but also any plans to get his car back on the road. Once the boys get the car back in the workshop they discover they have something very special on their hands as the Talbot turns out to be an ultra-rare factory proto type.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures S1E5
programme.desc: In his quest for world domination, Hitler oversaw the construction of the most advanced airplane of World War II, a fighter jet that would inspire a revolution in aerial warfare.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S1E5
programme.desc: This is a week of all things Argentinian. The dance troupe performs an Argentinian tango spectacle on the last night of the cruise and the chefs plan the gala feast with a themed menu. For the performers, the challenges are not only the dangerous acts involved in the show but also the drama during the rehearsal and the rough sea.

programme.title: 1989: The Year That Made Us E5
programme.desc: We didn't know it then, but in 1989, the digital age had begun. It was the year the first modern GPS satellites roamed above the earth, but most of us were looking down at another tech wonder that year: the Gameboy. The popular device paved the way for today's mobile lifestyle. Another little invention called the world wide web debuted in 1989 too. Filmmaker Kevin Smith and a host of tech insiders take you on a journey through space and time.

programme.title: 1989: The Year That Made Us E1
programme.desc: The War on Terror began in 2001, but the cause of this 17-year conflict can be traced back to 1989. In this episode of National Geographic's insightful 6-part series, former Secretary of State James Baker and retired General David Petraeus shed new light on the early birth of Islamic extremism in Afghanistan, and examine America's complex, on-going battle against this ever-changing ideological enemy that knows no borders.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S12E7
programme.desc: Keith Stansell is flying over the Colombian jungle on a US Government mission to locate hidden drug labs. Without warning, the plane's engine shuts down and the team are forced to crash-land. Keith and his crew are quickly surrounded by heavily armed FARC guerrillas. Two of the team are executed and Keith is taken hostage. For the next five and a half years, Keith endures back-breaking starvation marches, forced isolation, and torture.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E4
programme.desc: China's vast grasslands are a hard place to survive. Battered by ferocious and unpredictable storms throughout the year, the inhabitants of these grasslands have to be adaptable and tenacious to survive. During the short three-month window of summer, the plains residents have to race against time to raise their young before the onset of autumn and winter begin.

programme.title: The Lost Tomb Of Alexander The Great
programme.desc: Packed with present tense investigation and jaw-dropping revelations, this is the story of archaeologists Dr Geoffrey Tassie and Prof Emad Khalil's hunt to find Alexander the Great's final resting place.

programme.title: Ultimate Survival WWII E5
programme.desc: Survival expert Hazen Audel retraces the incredible survival journey of 4 American airmen, left stranded in Australia's remote Gulf Country after an ill-fated bombing mission during World War II. Hazen follows their desperate passage through one of the most isolated places on earth, as they navigated a brutal environment of deadly snakes, man eating crocs and searing heat, in a heroic attempt to get back to base.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S1E6
programme.desc: This is the final cruise for Captain Russo and he must have the Costa Serena in perfect running order before the handover to a new captain. There is also a new itinerary and a week of intensive safety tests keeping the crew busy before he disembarks. With a new route comes a change in the entertainment schedule as well. Preparations are in full swing for the final voyage of the season.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures S1E6
programme.desc: In the last desperate days of the Third Reich, the city of Berlin was turned into a citadel to protect Hitler. A 30ft (10 meters) underground fortress surrounded by 13ft (4 meters) thick concrete walls, it's safe from any attack the Allies can throw at him from the air.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E5
programme.desc: Meet China's most affectionate and vocal monkeys in the remote, seasonal forests of Central China. These mountain forests and all who live here, experience unpredictable and harsh weather in a land that can be covered in snow for 4 months of the year. Follow the journey of a baby Golden snub-nosed monkey during the first year of her life as she learns all about her forest home and battles the elements to survive.

programme.title: Tut's Treasures: The Last Pharaoh
programme.desc: The discovery of Tutankhamun's tomb in 1922 made headlines across the world sparking a global frenzy for Ancient Egypt. Crammed inside were over priceless artifacts of every type - from gold slippers to finely tooled daggers, the remains of chariots and the boy king's show-stopping solid gold death mask. But of all the 5,398 treasures from the tomb of Tutankhamun it's the ones that paint a picture of Tutankhamun's family that are the most unsettling. Particularly intriguing are two tiny mummified babies found in the tomb. Now being re-examined in the labs of the Grand Egyptian Museum, they give a chilling insight into the bizarre practices that kept the Pharaoh's dynasty in power and ultimately lead to its downfall. DNA analysis reveals the tiny fetuses are Tutankhamun's still born children - the offspring of an incestuous relationship between Tutankhamun and his sister. Similarly DNA evidence suggests Tutankhamun was also the result of incest whilst artifacts, hidden for yea.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S12E8
programme.desc: Canadian 21-year-old Christina Jocko is addicted to spending money, partying and taking drugs. But when she discovers opiates her life spirals into addiction. Out of work, out of money and out of luck - an offer of an easy $10,000 for running cocaine from Panama looks like a way out. But little does she realise the tempting adventure will cost her five years of her life.

programme.title: Alien Deep With Bob Ballard E1
programme.desc: Dr. Robert Ballard embarks on a journey like no other, making an underwater odyssey to the world's tallest mountain, Mauna Kea, in Hawaii. This Pacific giant stands 13,800ft above sea level, and reaches down a further 19,700ft into the deep. Dr. Ballard leads a two-submersible team right into the volcanic heart of the island.

programme.title: Brain Games S6E2
programme.desc: Actress Tiffany Haddish and director Jordan Peele join Keegan-Michael Key to play games that show how Hollywood pros manipulate our brains to make us feel genuine emotion while watching movies. Challenges and demos include taking a closer look at some of the bizarre tactics used to create sound effects in movies, spotting the stuntman, identifying a performer in disguise and illuminating how filmmakers manipulate our brains with editing. Sound designer Craig Pennigan shows us how sound alters the way our brains perceive a scene, Haddish tests her mental strength and agility in the Gauntlet, and mentalist Lior Suchard stuns the crowd with an amazing mind-reading trick.

programme.title: Big, Bigger, Biggest S3E5
programme.desc: Rising 610-metres tall, Canton Tower is the tallest television tower in the world. Explore engineering breakthroughs used in the construction of the Washington Monument, the Eiffel Tower, Canada's CN Tower and Canton Tower, each ingenious leap allowing engineers to build big, bigger and eventually biggest.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E9
programme.desc: The people of Kolkata are so intensely proud of their local cuisine, especially their epic street food. David meets up with Sneha, who takes him on a crazy food tour of the city. They ride the tram and do as the locals do on their quest to sample Kolkata's best street eats, including the famous Kati roll.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E10
programme.desc: Kolkata is home to India's largest Chinese community, which has been in existence for over 200 years, leaving a huge impact on the local food scene. They are fiercely proud of their Hakka-style cuisine and David can't wait to get his fill. He spends the day with a family that produces and sells their own Chinese sauce, eating their delicious momos and fried chicken.

programme.title: Alien Deep With Bob Ballard E2
programme.desc: Dr. Robert Ballard is on the hunt for the world's oldest shipwrecks in the Mediterranean Sea. Using tactics and technology developed over a 50-year career at sea, he is on a quest to uncover the lost history of the Ancient World. His journey takes him from the Mediterranean to Hawaii and the US, and he proves that the seas hold more treasure and history than all the world's museums combined.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E5
programme.desc: Police arrest a woman with cocaine taped directly to her body. This is called the 'mummy' method. Police race to her flight as there may be an accomplice. A man's suitcase is full of loose pepper and officers believe it's to confuse drug-sniffing dogs. A Russian carrier fears for his life and must be secretly moved to headquarters.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S19E2
programme.desc: A cargo jet plummets to earth in the Swedish Arctic. And as investigators pore over the evidence, a terrifying picture of chaos and confusion emerges.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E1
programme.desc: In the cold swamps of Georgia, Colbert is facing several months of bitter winter ahead of him. He realizes his window for getting meat is quickly closing and a winter struggling for protein would be excruciating. In a remote spot in southern Utah, Matt returns home to his pit house to discover the land has changed. He needs to check his resources and assess if he'll have enough to survive through the colder months.

programme.title: Ultimate Survival WWII E6
programme.desc: Survival expert Hazen Audel is in the Solomons, a far-flung chain of Pacific islands, to retrace the incredible 43-day survival journey of Lt. Hugh Miller. Shipwrecked during WWII, Miller faced-off against shark-infested waters, miles of thick jungle and a Japanese enemy determined to hunt him down. Armed with the same equipment, Hazen pits himself against this punishing environment, pushing himself and his bushcraft skills in the ultimate test.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E11
programme.desc: David finally fulfills his dream of visiting the Golden Temple, the holiest Sikh gurudwara in the world. The langar inside the Golden Temple, where the community comes and cooks together, serves upwards of 100,000 people a day and David gets to experience the mania of the meal preparation firsthand. Later, David takes a local food tour to sample all of the local Punjabi delicacies.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E12
programme.desc: David is in Amritsar - a city known for the warmth of its people and its amazing food - exploring all the different facets of Punjabi culture. He meets up with some locals, tries specialty Punjabi dishes and even learns to tie his own turban. He also spends time with two contrasting local families: one is vegetarian and the other loves their meat.

programme.title: Big, Bigger, Biggest S3E6
programme.desc: The French Train a Grande Vitesse, known as the TGV, regularly reaches speeds exceeding 300 kilometers per hour. Explore the historical breakthroughs and inner workings of the 4 iconic trains, each one a major technological innovation that allowed trains to go faster, and from big, to bigger and eventually biggest.

programme.title: Air Crash Investigation S19E8
programme.desc: A turboprop commuter plane is approaching a remote airport in Papua, Indonesia, when it mysteriously disappears. Billowing smoke on a nearby mountaintop leads search-and-rescue teams to the wreckage. And while three separate systems could have prevented the tragedy, it's up to investigators to figure out why none of them did.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E2
programme.desc: There are only a few days left of deer hunting season in the Blue Ridge Mountains of North Carolina, and homesteaders Tony and Amelia need meat to get them through the cold winter. But Tony has never been deer hunting before and doesn't have the luxury of time to hone his methods. Tony is thrown right in to the hunt, and the pressure is on.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E6
programme.desc: A woman's bag is flagged in the x-ray area but she's already been inspected twice. Police must decide whether to tear the bag apart or let her go. An Italian man claims not to understand the police. He may be telling the truth. Or he may be trying to evade the law. A shipment of children's toys may hide a stash of cocaine.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E13
programme.desc: A trip to Assam is not actually complete without visiting the island of Majuli. On this ever shrinking island Pablo gets to witness the two sides of it. On one hand Pablo meets another prominent tribe of Assam: The Mishing. Houses on stilts, weaving their own clothes, Mishing share their authentic recipe of Apong- the very famous home brewed rice beer with Pablo.

programme.title: Fearless Chef E7
programme.desc: The Fearless Chef ventures into the isolated Amazonian jungle of Peru with the Huachipaeri and Matsiguenka tribes, where he samples termites, worms and a host of medicinal plants.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E25
programme.desc: Ben catches up with the organisation founder of Produce to the People, Penelope Dodd. Penelope takes Ben on a tour around the farm, picking fresh produce for Ben to use in one of his recipes. Ben decides to make a fresh bruschetta, adding his own twist by swapping out the bread for a charcoal lavosh cracker.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E26
programme.desc: Ben makes a Stripey Sashimi with a Truffle and Macadamia Gazpacho. At the University of Queensland, Ben and Joel attempt to recreate a Satay Chicken that Ben had on his travels in Hong Kong. Throughout the cook the boys discuss how an induction cooker works.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E8
programme.desc: Oaxaca is the undisputed culinary capital of Mexico, and Peter Kuruvita spends a week here sampling all this city has to offer, from cheese to tamales and even a serving of grasshoppers.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E7
programme.desc: Peter Kuruvita arrives in the coastal state of Veracruz where he discovers the technique of smoking jalapenos into chipotles, before visiting the original home of vanilla.

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S2E12
programme.desc: In this episode of Miguel's Feasts: Miguel's delicious crayfish roll, tasty bbq ribs for a great bunch of volunteers, the great schnitzel challenge, and the latest buzz on where to find the best Aussie honey!

programme.title: Miguel's Feasts S2E13
programme.desc: In this episode of Miguel's Feasts: Farm fresh produce with real bite, Miguel puts his churros up against some tasty donuts, a seaside classic you can make at home and an easy Mother's day treat that kids can – Meatloaf with love!

programme.title: Dive Detectives E4
programme.desc: With the advanced ship simulators, the Dive Detectives reconstruct the Great Lakes freighter, Edmund Fitzgerald's final hours against a rogue wave.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E3
programme.desc: Sara continues her journey in a cruise on the Yellow Water. She immerses herself in Murumburr culture by joining the aboriginal ladies cook in their traditional way. Then, Sara enjoys a traditional Greek lunch with octopus bashing to learn about Darwin's Greek culture. After exploring the ancient culture and outback life, Sara finds out more about the modern lifestyle, bar-hopping with helicopters.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E4
programme.sub-title: Broome - The Pearl Of Western Australia
programme.desc: Broome's past and present revolve around pearls, so Sara visits a pearl farm and sees how these diamonds of the ocean are grown and tries out amazing boutique pearl necklaces made for a queen. Then, Sara is invited to taste the innovative creation of an Australian-Asian fusion feast. Sara gets inspired by the dish and decides to pamper her hosts with a creative oyster dish.

programme.title: John Torode's Malaysian Adventure E7
programme.desc: John's Malaysian Adventure takes him to the northeastern city of Kota Bharu, where the strong Islamic influences are closely reflected in the food. Local guide Addie Chan presents several traditional techniques for cooking unusual Malaysian delicacies like meat floss while roadside shop owner Kak Pah demonstrates the proper way of making the classic Solak Lada.

programme.title: Dive Detectives E5
programme.desc: The Dive Detectives brave pirate and shark infested waters to try and locate the missing subs of WWII and find out why they sunk.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E5
programme.desc: Sara drives a jeep through the flooding Pentecost River to East Kimberley, soaking in unforgettable scenery of the Cockburn Range Mountain. She arrives at Home Valley, a sustainable and tourist destination to meet aboriginals. Whilst enjoying the outback lifestyle at Home Valley with bushwalks and fishing, Sara is inspired by the communal spirit to prepare a wooden-fire oven crocodile pizza.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E6
programme.desc: Sara meets up with a local blogger Kartika to kick off her Broome tour. After learning the multicultural history of Broome, Sara is excited to know more and invites Neville, one of the last remaining pearl divers, to cook a 'luggers' lunch together on the pearl diving boats. After a successful hunt in the knee-deep muddy waters, Sara cooks the crab on the famous cable beach.

programme.title: John Torode's Malaysian Adventure E8
programme.desc: Guide Basira Yuseff introduces John to the wide array of traditional delicacies available at a popular street food market in Kuala Lumpur including a snack with his name on it, Roti John! He then visits a local chef who has shaken up the dining scene with his innovative takes on classic Malaysian dishes before going back to the UK to prepare a chicken curry dish with TV chef Carolina.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E14
programme.desc: Pablo explores more about Tiwas of Tharakunchi after learning that they are divided into two: The Tiwas of the Hills and Tiwas of the Plains. While he gets a chance to be among the Tiwas during the festivities Pablo is just blown away as he gets to know more about their food, cooking techniques, and their societal views.

programme.title: Fearless Chef E8
programme.desc: The Fearless Chef braves the frozen bleak wilderness of Western Mongolia where he joins the Kazakh eagle hunters on a quest for wild rabbit on horseback.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E35
programme.desc: Staying in a beautiful accommodation by the sea, Ben makes his easy, no mess Fajita Baked Salmon. Joel meets Ben by discussing a fun fact about physics and spatulas, giving a trick to try at home. Their location is the Union College where they put their ‘zucchini spiralizer' to the test for a yummy, simple dish.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E36
programme.desc: Ben shows us a super simple, cheap and easy dip that is a sure winner at any dinner party. Ben and Joel discuss the differences between raw garlic and cooked garlic and how to decide between which to cook with.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E9
programme.desc: Peter Kuruvita arrives in the Mayan stronghold of the Yucatan Peninsula, major producer of one of the hottest chillies on earth - the Habanero, before heading to the state of Tabasco where chocolate has been consumed for thousands of years.

programme.desc: Peter and Jeff grew up near the Yangtze as boys, and now they are returning to the Three Gorges for one last look before the land that inspired poets and artists for centuries is consumed by the rising waters. The Government is building the world's biggest dam on the Yangtze in this region, displacing millions of people from their homes.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E2
programme.desc: Grains and the discovery of how to grow and cook them allowed man to end his hunter-gatherer practices. Today, civilization takes grains for granted and in this hour, we'll explain why that might be a somewhat shortsighted approach! Bread, beer, pasta, pizza, noodles and rice make the world go 'round and every culture has some kind of variation on these culinary themes.

programme.title: Route Awakening S1E4
programme.desc: Harry is in the Tibetan plateau to learn Tibetan archery. In a village in Ledu County, he meets a master preparing him for a local tournament and learns to appreciate the craft of making bow and arrow and the pre-competition ceremony involving traditional dancing and howling. Down towards Xunhua, he meets a tribe with Kazakhstan origins and learns the traditional methods of making goat skin buoys.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E7

programme.title: Food Lab S2E27
programme.desc: Ben calls into Freycinet Marine Farm to pick up some fresh scallops. Back at Avalon Coastal Retreat, Ben puts together a Scallop Tartare, using Freycinet's fresh scallops, pairing them with a chorizo oil dressing. Using one of his favourite ingredients from his garden, Ben then makes an Upside-down Rhubarb Cake.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E28
programme.desc: Ben sets up for a cook in front of the picturesque view at Edge of the Bay. He prepares a Potato Salad perfect for a summer's night BBQ, taking it up a notch with the addition of Hot Smoked Salmon. At the University of Queensland, Ben is missing his partner in crime, Joel Gilmore. At the end of a long day, Ben makes a Blueberry drizzle cake and places it in Frankie the Food Trunk to bake.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E1
programme.desc: First stop, Xi'an, the starting point of the ancient silk road network and the national food capital of China. With its reputation as one of China's holy grail for foodies, Jamie can't wait to get stuck in to all the exotic flavours from China's central plains and western regions! His taste buds are in for a treat! As well as learning the best amazing dishes this ancient charming city has inherited for thousands of years, he will be knocking up a feast for the new rocker friends and jamming with a rock band!

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E2
programme.desc: Next up on Jamie's silk road food trek, he will travel to Heyang that is well known for being home to some of China's most ancient cooking techniques. He will meet the best local chefs to find out about the oldest Chinese recipes, have a lesson in the art of “bun flower” making and get his hands dirty in the fields in search of the finest ingredients. To top it all off, love is in the air as he experiences a once in a lifetime countryside wedding!

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E5
programme.desc: Parents across the country are finding it increasingly difficult to prise their children away from their mobile devices but Dai Saunders has a plan. He's designed a spectacular crafting workshop for the end of his garden so that the whole family can role their sleeves up and get making. It's an ingenious design that hides the space from the house, camouflaged under a sweeping, sedum roof and the whole family are going to pitch in to make it.

programme.title: Somewhere In China E3
programme.desc: Peter and Jeff Hutchens revisit the cold city of their youth, Harbin. Despite its communist roots, Harbin has become a vibrant commercial city that has come to embrace its icy heritage. The brothers swim in icy waters, make an ice sculpture, race down an ice slide, and drink in a bar made of ice, then visit the world famous Harbin Ice Festival.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E3
programme.desc: High protein, omega-rich seafood saved our species from its first threat of extinction, funded the American Revolution, and increasingly fuels our brains and muscle today. Market fish like cod and tuna defined entire eras of history but unsustainable practices are forcing us to redefine our commercial goals in the ocean. Current demand necessitates a change in our attitudes toward seafood.

programme.title: Route Awakening S1E5
programme.desc: The journey continues along the course of the Yellow River. Harry is now with Camel nomads in the Alxa League, Inner Mongolia where he aims for the million dollar shot with camels against sunset. He also learns that it does rain in the desert and that crops do grow. Plus, he finds out more about Suo Suo and Congrong, the cash crop that would replace the traditional herding ways of desert nomads.

programme.title: Peter Kuruvita's Mexican Fiesta E8
programme.desc: Oaxaca is the undisputed culinary capital of Mexico, and Peter Kuruvita spends a week here sampling all this city has to offer, from cheese to tamales and even a serving of grasshoppers.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E7
programme.desc: After touring the outback, Sara arrives in Melbourne and discovers a bar which can only be accessed through a secret door and a cinema overlooking the city's skyscrapers at night. Then, she joins the local community in an annual polo game where city slickers and rural cowboys compete on their riding skills. Finally, she finds out the secret of Michelin-star quality wagyu beef from the stockmen.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E8
programme.desc: Sara drives along the Great Ocean Road and arrives in surf country - Victoria. She discovers a supreme olive oil and reveals the secrets behind the peppery flavor. Surrounded by a vast array of vegetables and fruits, Sara decides to pay tribute to the fresh and natural ingredients by dishing up a salad using indigenous pistachio, local wine and peppery olive oil.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E37
programme.desc: Ben discusses the benefits to cooking with ethical free range chicken, and then teaches us how to break down a whole bird in a way that limits wastage. Ben then meets friend and scientist Joel and talk through a quick and easy pickling recipe to avoid wasted fresh vegetables at home.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E38
programme.desc: Ben and the crew head down to the beautiful East Coast of Tasmania, where he attempts to cook the 'perfect steak'. He leaves the steak on a bed of salt for two hours before cooking and explains it results in increased flavour, and a nice crust on top.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E3
programme.desc: Wuzhong, home to the largest Muslim community on the silk road, and of course China's best place to enjoy Chinese halal food. Jamie will learn an unusual breakfast recipe that's certainly not for the faint-hearted and face his hardest noodle challenge yet. He also will uncover the secrets to the healthy yellow riverbank lifestyle that's helped shape the rich culinary history here an also got the younger generation rethinking their diets.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E4
programme.desc: Next stop, Dunhuang, the last city that trade merchants would pass through on the ancient silk road before braving the desert. Jamie will be introduced to the wonders of desert lifestyle to find out how the harsh local terrain has helped to^shape the unique food culture. It will definitely be a crazy ride by spending one day with a caravan of camels and, but all the pay is worth it. Jamie will cook in the VIP desert kitchen and attempt to make the hardest dish to date, for celebrating the unforgettable birthday party.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E6
programme.desc: Down on the sunny coast of Cornwall, world-class, adaptive surfer Peg Leg, wants to do a very unique extension – to his VW campervan home. Peg lives in his van full time and has travelled everywhere from the Arctic Circle to the Sahara desert in search of the best waves on the planet. Despite having no technical training he's hoping to transform his home on wheels by building a new cabin from scratch, for him and his 5 year old daughter, Bluebell.

programme.desc: Oaxaca is the undisputed culinary capital of Mexico, and Peter Kuruvita spends a week here sampling all this city has to offer, from cheese to tamales and even a serving of grasshoppers.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E7
programme.desc: After touring the outback, Sara arrives in Melbourne and discovers a bar which can only be accessed through a secret door and a cinema overlooking the city's skyscrapers at night. Then, she joins the local community in an annual polo game where city slickers and rural cowboys compete on their riding skills. Finally, she finds out the secret of Michelin-star quality wagyu beef from the stockmen.

programme.title: Sara's Australia Unveiled E8
programme.desc: Sara drives along the Great Ocean Road and arrives in surf country - Victoria. She discovers a supreme olive oil and reveals the secrets behind the peppery flavor. Surrounded by a vast array of vegetables and fruits, Sara decides to pay tribute to the fresh and natural ingredients by dishing up a salad using indigenous pistachio, local wine and peppery olive oil.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E37
programme.desc: Ben discusses the benefits to cooking with ethical free range chicken, and then teaches us how to break down a whole bird in a way that limits wastage. Ben then meets friend and scientist Joel and talk through a quick and easy pickling recipe to avoid wasted fresh vegetables at home.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E38
programme.desc: Ben and the crew head down to the beautiful East Coast of Tasmania, where he attempts to cook the 'perfect steak'. He leaves the steak on a bed of salt for two hours before cooking and explains it results in increased flavour, and a nice crust on top.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E3
programme.desc: Wuzhong, home to the largest Muslim community on the silk road, and of course China's best place to enjoy Chinese halal food. Jamie will learn an unusual breakfast recipe that's certainly not for the faint-hearted and face his hardest noodle challenge yet. He also will uncover the secrets to the healthy yellow riverbank lifestyle that's helped shape the rich culinary history here an also got the younger generation rethinking their diets.

programme.title: Delicacy Hunter: On The Silk Road S1E4
programme.desc: Next stop, Dunhuang, the last city that trade merchants would pass through on the ancient silk road before braving the desert. Jamie will be introduced to the wonders of desert lifestyle to find out how the harsh local terrain has helped to^shape the unique food culture. It will definitely be a crazy ride by spending one day with a caravan of camels and, but all the pay is worth it. Jamie will cook in the VIP desert kitchen and attempt to make the hardest dish to date, for celebrating the unforgettable birthday party.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S7E6
programme.desc: Down on the sunny coast of Cornwall, world-class, adaptive surfer Peg Leg, wants to do a very unique extension – to his VW campervan home. Peg lives in his van full time and has travelled everywhere from the Arctic Circle to the Sahara desert in search of the best waves on the planet. Despite having no technical training he's hoping to transform his home on wheels by building a new cabin from scratch, for him and his 5 year old daughter, Bluebell.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S1E1
programme.desc: After a hectic summer, the Costa Serena sets sail from Venice and faces new challenges: honeymoon season. With major staff changes, brand new entertainers, worsening weather and several unexpected challenges ahead, this cruise must be on high alert. But before embarking on the new adventure, there is a lot to be done for the crew and the maintenance team.

programme.title: Pond Stars E6
programme.desc: The Pond Stars come out of their shell in Atlanta tackling two wild projects in just five days. Their first job is at an environmental center, creating a pond specifically for rescued turtles as an outdoor classroom for an upcoming kids camp. The second project is to build a 35-foot waterfall and 600-gallon reservoir that will have wildlife flocking to this suburban backyard, for the birds.

programme.title: Celebrity Chef: East Vs West E1
programme.desc: 2 Celebrity Chefs. 1 iconic local dish and only 1 winner. Let the cook-off begin!

programme.title: Celebrity Chef: East Vs West E2
programme.desc: The battle continues as our two chefs head to Shunde, China and take on its most iconic dish.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E3
programme.desc: High protein, omega-rich seafood saved our species from its first threat of extinction, funded the American Revolution, and increasingly fuels our brains and muscle today. Market fish like cod and tuna defined entire eras of history but unsustainable practices are forcing us to redefine our commercial goals in the ocean. Current demand necessitates a change in our attitudes toward seafood.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E29
programme.desc: Ben and the crew stop at the Freycinet Marine Farm to pick up some fresh oysters on the way to their accommodation. After the crew are settled in, Ben prepares a refreshing canape of Oyster in a wakame flake dressing. Next, Joel explains the science involved in making a quick and simple Mayonnaise. Half way through the recipes, Joel splits the mayonnaise and has to ask Ben for some help to save the recipe.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E30
programme.desc: Ben makes a fantastic little savoury breakfast dish of Salmon Rillette served on fresh sourdough. At the University of Queensland, Ben uses some excess fruit to make a delicious fruity berry apple jam. Perfect to add to your morning porridge or serve with some sneaky dessert. Joel Gilmore explains a little more about Ben using the pectin from the apples to thicken his jam.

programme.title: Bangkok Airport E3
programme.desc: Bangkok Airport is a friendly place with helpful staff but misunderstandings can still arise as it serves millions of passengers from around the world. There will always be a language barrier as seen with a French mum turned away from her flight, a man losing his juggling sticks, a bossy immigration officer fighting a one-woman war on queue jumping and a French tourist facing deportation.

programme.title: John Torode's Malaysian Adventure E7
programme.desc: John's Malaysian Adventure takes him to the northeastern city of Kota Bharu, where the strong Islamic influences are closely reflected in the food. Local guide Addie Chan presents several traditional techniques for cooking unusual Malaysian delicacies like meat floss while roadside shop owner Kak Pah demonstrates the proper way of making the classic Solak Lada.

programme.title: Route Awakening S1E4
programme.desc: Harry is in the Tibetan plateau to learn Tibetan archery. In a village in Ledu County, he meets a master preparing him for a local tournament and learns to appreciate the craft of making bow and arrow and the pre-competition ceremony involving traditional dancing and howling. Down towards Xunhua, he meets a tribe with Kazakhstan origins and learns the traditional methods of making goat skin buoys.

programme.title: Cruise Ship Diaries S1E2
programme.desc: The ship faces a tough week with worsening weather, a safety inspection putting jobs on the line, unusual guests and many unexpected challenges. Hotel Director Attilio Sissa is on board to ensure food and beverage safety of the ship's bars and restaurants. Later in the grand bar some gentlemen undergo extreme makeover for a talent contest while the entertainers are preparing for a big show.

programme.title: Heathrow S4E1
programme.desc: King of the Passenger Experience Manager, Demi, dealing with some disgruntled Passengers, Check in Girls Carrie- Anne and Selina juggling love lives and broken baggage belts, and discover if Border Force Bob will let a young Brazilian student into the UK to visit his brother?

programme.title: Heathrow S4E2
programme.desc: At Heathrow a plane takes off or lands every 45 seconds and in this episode we learn the secrets of parking planes with a rookie and his ping pong bats. The King and Queen of Terminal 2, Demi and Sue, wrestle with a bare chested drunk and back at immigration Kat and Bob come across a visitor whose reason for entering the UK just doesn't add up.

programme.title: Celebrity Chef: East Vs West E3
programme.desc: It's the culinary Thrilla in Manila as the celebrity chefs head to the Philippines.

programme.title: Celebrity Chef: East Vs West E4
programme.sub-title: If You Can't Stand The Heat, Get Out Of The Kitche
programme.desc: The temperature rises as the battle continues in sunny Ipoh, Malaysia.

programme.title: Eat: The Story Of Food E4
programme.desc: Christopher Columbus. Julia Child. Clarence Birdseye. These are some of the revolutionary men and women who have changed what and how we eat, remaking not just food history but human history. Some of these food revolutionaries are well known, others obscure. But one thing they have in common is that they have fundamentally shaped how we live today.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E39
programme.desc: Ben and the crew travel down to Hobart to begin their Hobart food crawl, led by Rhys Hannan, Head Chef and Owner at Small-Fry. Their first stop is Pigeon Hole Cafe, a busy cafe in West Hobart where everyone can experience a true paddock to plate experience. Next Ben makes his version of popcorn chicken with Joel.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E40
programme.desc: Ben and Rhys head to the second stop on their Hobart food crawl, Pigeon Whole Bakery. Similar name to the first location however the bakery offers many different sweet delights, an abundance of breads, fresh lunch items and an incredible home-made lemonade, as well as offering all of the bakery good wholesale - hence the pigeon whole name.

programme.title: Bangkok Airport E4
programme.desc: It is Valentine's Day at the airport. Romance blossoms for immigration officers Bert and Nat, Captain Jack shares the secrets of a successful marriage and there are free hugs for every passenger. Justin jets in for cosmetic surgery to perk up his love life, Nathan introduces his parents to his new Thai boyfriend and a Swiss traveler flies to Thailand to meet his internet girlfriend.

programme.title: John Torode's Malaysian Adventure E8
programme.desc: Guide Basira Yuseff introduces John to the wide array of traditional delicacies available at a popular street food market in Kuala Lumpur including a snack with his name on it, Roti John! He then visits a local chef who has shaken up the dining scene with his innovative takes on classic Malaysian dishes before going back to the UK to prepare a chicken curry dish with TV chef Carolina.

programme.title: Route Awakening S1E5
programme.desc: The journey continues along the course of the Yellow River. Harry is now with Camel nomads in the Alxa League, Inner Mongolia where he aims for the million dollar shot with camels against sunset. He also learns that it does rain in the desert and that crops do grow. Plus, he finds out more about Suo Suo and Congrong, the cash crop that would replace the traditional herding ways of desert nomads.

programme.title: Megafish
programme.desc: We follow explorer Zeb Hogan into the heart of Southeast Asia, where he searches the mighty Mekong River for megafish species.

programme.title: Africa's Deadliest S4E3
programme.desc: In the African bush every animal, young and old, is in a fight for its life. In the grasslands of Botswana, this brutal arms race means the difference between death and glory. Each has their own tactics and weapons that will either protect or kill. It's a finely balanced contest - the winners win big, but for the losers - its game over. There's no room for second best and only those at the top of their game will survive.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S3E3
programme.desc: Snake catchers Simon Keys and Siouxsie Gillett race across Snake Cities to cope with the venomous and swift hunters. They fish out a massive Black Mamba from a pool, hand wrestle the largest cobra in Africa and face off against an angry neighbor to retrieve an exotic Boa constrictor. Every move may end up a lethal bite in the limbs or head.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S5E1
programme.desc: In this explosive episode of Animal Fight Club, we expose how some of the most deadly battles in the animal kingdom are fought amongst the same species, as well as between predator and prey. Using exclusive new user generated footage and material from top wildlife film makers, we show that mortal danger often comes from where you least expect, and animals will go to any lengths to eat, protect their young, or pass on their bloodline.

programme.title: Dead By Dawn E2
programme.desc: At night, the dunes of the Arabian desert come to life with unique animals specially adapted to thrive in this hostile environment, from lizards that swim under the sand to spiders that can run ten miles per hour.

programme.title: Legendary Catch E6
programme.desc: Carter Andrews travels to one of the most diverse aquatic environments in the country, America's Gulf Coast, to search for legendary Alligator Gar. Reaching lengths of 10 feet and weights of over 300 pounds, the Alligator Gar has long been intertwined with Cajun culture, garnering a fearsome reputation as an aggressive apex predator because of its crocodilian snout and sharp teeth. Starting his journey in Louisiana, Carter tracks down some legends locals say still haunt the rivers and bayous and learns there's much more than meets the eye to these prehistoric fish. Following leads from Cajun Country into Texas, Carter searches for giant gar in Texan waterways some say still house the biggest gar in the United States.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E6
programme.desc: Dr. Larry Kawa's office doubles as an orthodontics practice and a multi-aquarium showcase featuring all kinds of rare marine life. Living Color is commissioned to replace the physical tank, and also provide a unique underwater specimen to display. Mat and Francis are stumped and have to dig deep to come up with what is known as a Mermaid's Purse.

programme.title: Africa's Deadliest: Botswana Compilations E3
programme.desc: When you are surrounded by Africa's Deadliest, there can be safety in numbers. Having the protection of fierce group can make the difference between life and death for some animals. But aggression directed outwards can sometimes turn inwards. In this unforgiving land, fierce families fight others, and sometimes amongst themselves, to survive.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S3E5
programme.desc: Snake catchers Simon and Siouxsie discover an 8-foot black mamba after destroying a kitchen for a harmless house snake. Then, they receive a call from a shopping mall that the Africa's largest cobra is loose and causing panic. Finally, a mechanic discovers a deadly snake in his toolbox and it makes his blood cold.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S5E2
programme.desc: In this dramatic episode of Animal Fight Club, wildlife goes to war, from miniature murderers to the biggest brutes. Using under-the-skin CGI and compelling wildlife footage from some of the world's best documentary makers, we uncover the tactics and strategies behind the brawls. From African plains to the snow-covered wilds of North America, we reveal how nature's deadliest battles are fought over turf, dominance and the right to mate.

programme.title: Savage Kingdom S3E2
programme.desc: Trapped by the rising flood waters, Dikeledi must teach her wayward cubs the lessons of survival. But this brutal Kingdom is no place for a gentle cheetah family. The rotten clan of hyenas have taken control. There is one foe that will not lie down and tolerate their tyranny - the formidable Makulu Pack. These Wild Dogs have the cunning and experience, but with an ageing leader their strength soon starts to crumble from within and others are waiting to seize their opportunity.

programme.title: Legendary Catch E2
programme.desc: Carter is in the Bolivian jungle in pursuit of a mythical fish that's known for its strength and razor sharp teeth - The Golden Dorado. Pushing himself to the limit, Carter and a local native chief paddle dugout canoes and trek days up a secluded river to an ancient waterfall in the hopes of hooking one of these mystical fish. A formidable foe, Carter sees Dorado and can't hook them. When he can hook a Dorado it's not the legendary size he's after. With supplies running low for his journey, will Carter catch the Dorado he's after?

programme.title: Shark Island
programme.desc: Enric Sala and his team are on a mission to dive the protected waters of Cocos National Park off the western coast of mainland Costa Rica. Dive the mysterious Las Gamelas seamounts and free sharks, turtles and tunas caught on illegal fishing lines. It's all part of an effort to understand how over-fishing affects shark populations and what happens to eco-systems when the sharks disappear.

programme.title: Africa's Deadliest S4E4
programme.desc: In a constant battle to survive, animals have developed a range of superpowers that give them the best chance in the deadly games that play out across the Kalahari. Largely undetectable to humans, this film reveals a hidden world of indestructible weaponry, incredible strength, ingenious adaptations and magnified senses - extraordinary abilities that catapult these animals into the realm of superheroes., and animals will go to any lengths to eat, protect their young, or pass on their bloodline.

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E5
programme.desc: A young reindeer with many ailments needs Dr. Oakley's help to get back into fighting shape and an elderly porcupine poses a pokey problem.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E1
programme.desc: This episode of Unlikely Animal Friends features heartwarming stories of a two-legged chihuahua who befriends a silkie chicken, an adventurous mountaineer and his rock-climbing cat, and a goat who refuses to leave his beloved donkey's side. These stories profile the most unique, most surprising, and most loving animal friendships.

programme.title: Giant Carnivorous Bats
programme.desc: National Geographic Photographer and Emerging Explorer Anand Varma teams with Dr. Rodrigo Medellin, a world-renowned ecologist and National Geographic Society grantee, in search of two large, rare, and carnivorous bat species, 'Vampyrum Spectrum' and 'Chrotopterus Auritus,' in the ancient Mayan heartland of southern Mexico.

programme.title: Wild Indochina
programme.desc: Indochina; three ancient kingdoms, Laos, Vietnam and Cambodia, linked by one great river: the mighty Mekong. A mystical land shaped by the forces of the monsoon. A region ravaged by war but, like a Phoenix, risen from the ashes. Within its boundaries can be found one tenth of the world's species, and some of the richest ecosystems on the planet. This is the land of the Mother River, one of the most bio diverse regions on Earth.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E4
programme.desc: Living Color is commissioned to create the centerpiece for a beach home on Grand Cayman Island. They envision a giant aquarium featuring marine life of the surrounding waters, but removing ornamental fish from Cayman waters is illegal. Mat Roy places resident fish expert Francis at the helm. With his encyclopedic knowledge of fish, this job should be a breeze.

programme.title: Africa's Deadliest Compilations E1
programme.desc: On land, Africa's predators rule supreme but there's no beating the battles fought under its seas. Under crashing waves and violent currents, formidable creatures are fighting battles to the death every day: from vast, spinning bait balls of sardines all the way to the deadliest at the top of the food chain--- where orcas and great white sharks fight for top position.

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E6
programme.desc: Dr. Oakley sees two stubborn muskoxen and a particularly wily coyote. A badly burned dog receives an innovative, if fishy, new treatment.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S4E2
programme.sub-title: The Tale Of The Cockatoo And The Kitty Cat
programme.desc: In this episode, we'll present you a cockatoo that enjoys giving massages to her once-feral feline friend, a California man who hangs ten with his surfing goat, and a hunting dog whose best friend and co-worker is a two-and-a-half-foot tall Eurasian eagle owl.

programme.title: World's Weirdest Compilations E2
programme.desc: The birds and the bees have never been so wild. Get ready for alien romance, bizarre reproduction and creative concepts in parenting.

programme.title: Untamed Philippines E1
programme.desc: We start on the tiny island of Batan, meeting a unique viper and a ubiquitous but also giant, land crab. Luzon is the main island of the Philippines. We drop in to Mindoro to see the most endangered large mammal in the Philippines, the tamaraw. The bustling capital of Manila dominates the centre of this large island but despite encroachments, huge areas of wilderness still exist. Here we meet blue tarantulas and strange forest birds. In the town of Pulilan we join a celebration that centres on the carabao, water buffalo. In the Verde Passage we join a group of photographers surveying the marine creatures of the area, from frog fish to pygmy seahorses. We also meet the people who have dedicated their lives to saving the most endangered crocodile in the world. On Palawan we find new sea creatures that charm and awe eco-tourists and take a trip along the longest navigable underground river to meet bats and swiftlets. We discover the sad recent history of the Palawan forest turtl.

programme.desc: In this episode, we'll present you a cockatoo that enjoys giving massages to her once-feral feline friend, a California man who hangs ten with his surfing goat, and a hunting dog whose best friend and co-worker is a two-and-a-half-foot tall Eurasian eagle owl.

programme.title: World's Weirdest Compilations E2
programme.desc: The birds and the bees have never been so wild. Get ready for alien romance, bizarre reproduction and creative concepts in parenting.

programme.title: Untamed Philippines E1
programme.desc: We start on the tiny island of Batan, meeting a unique viper and a ubiquitous but also giant, land crab. Luzon is the main island of the Philippines. We drop in to Mindoro to see the most endangered large mammal in the Philippines, the tamaraw. The bustling capital of Manila dominates the centre of this large island but despite encroachments, huge areas of wilderness still exist. Here we meet blue tarantulas and strange forest birds. In the town of Pulilan we join a celebration that centres on the carabao, water buffalo. In the Verde Passage we join a group of photographers surveying the marine creatures of the area, from frog fish to pygmy seahorses. We also meet the people who have dedicated their lives to saving the most endangered crocodile in the world. On Palawan we find new sea creatures that charm and awe eco-tourists and take a trip along the longest navigable underground river to meet bats and swiftlets. We discover the sad recent history of the Palawan forest turtl.

programme.title: Fish Tank Kings S2E4
programme.desc: Living Color is commissioned to create the centerpiece for a beach home on Grand Cayman Island. They envision a giant aquarium featuring marine life of the surrounding waters, but removing ornamental fish from Cayman waters is illegal. Mat Roy places resident fish expert Francis at the helm. With his encyclopedic knowledge of fish, this job should be a breeze.

programme.title: Africa's Deadliest Compilations E1
programme.desc: On land, Africa's predators rule supreme but there's no beating the battles fought under its seas. Under crashing waves and violent currents, formidable creatures are fighting battles to the death every day: from vast, spinning bait balls of sardines all the way to the deadliest at the top of the food chain--- where orcas and great white sharks fight for top position.

programme.title: Dr Oakley: Yukon Vet S6E6

programme.title: Shark Alley
programme.desc: Every year hundreds of sharks gather together in one of the most diverse convergence of species in the world. These predators follow a trail of millions of sardines as they migrate up the southern coast of Africa, where cape fur seals have gathered on Seal Island. As the seals begin their hunt, the sharks close in, culminating in a humongous feeding frenzy. Welcome to the shark alley!

Ready or not - the countdown has begun.
